WEBVTT

00:08.259 --> 00:10.845
You missed another episode of
"Shameless," and now we got

00:10.845 --> 00:13.180
to take valuable time out of our
show to tell you what the hell

00:13.180 --> 00:15.266
you missed 'cause you were too
damn lazy to get up off

00:15.266 --> 00:17.810
your fat asses
and watch the damn TV?

00:17.810 --> 00:19.395
We're both consenting adults.

00:19.395 --> 00:23.065
Separated by two decades,
a husband, and tenure.

00:23.065 --> 00:25.276
[grunts] What the fuck
was that for?

00:25.276 --> 00:26.861
Making me fall in love
with you.

00:26.861 --> 00:29.405
- Hi, Aunt Fiona.
- Holy shit.

00:29.405 --> 00:31.031
I forgot about the swastika.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.908
- Hey, what's your name again?
- Ian.

00:32.908 --> 00:35.120
When Caleb's not here, he's in
his sculpture studio.

00:35.120 --> 00:37.037
You ever let anyone visit
your studio?

00:37.037 --> 00:38.289
I would if anyone cared.

00:38.289 --> 00:40.040
Frank Gallagher,
cancer concierge.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.709
You got help with the kids?

00:41.709 --> 00:45.129
I have a lead on potential
employment for you.

00:45.129 --> 00:48.048
You're setting me up
with a dying woman's husband?

00:48.048 --> 00:50.468
He'll need a shoulder
to lean on

00:50.468 --> 00:52.137
and then to sleep on.

00:52.137 --> 00:54.472
[scoffs] I'm leaving.

00:54.472 --> 00:57.057
Hi.
Sorry I'm late.

00:57.057 --> 00:58.684
Yanis, what are you doing?

00:58.684 --> 01:00.519
Hey, put that down
so we can work on

01:00.519 --> 01:03.355
our extra strong friendship!
[yells]

01:03.355 --> 01:05.065
- [yelling]
- Holy shit!

01:05.065 --> 01:06.901
[exhales]

01:06.901 --> 01:09.236
Eviction notice?
Are you kidding me?

01:09.236 --> 01:11.030
The house is being sold
at auction.

01:11.030 --> 01:12.281
I do have some savings
I could kick in.

01:12.281 --> 01:14.408
No, no, no.
It's a Gallagher thing.

01:14.408 --> 01:16.035
[Sean] You lose the house, it's
gonna be somebody else's thing.

01:16.035 --> 01:17.244
- Hurry up.
- We're gonna lose it.

01:17.244 --> 01:18.496
$130,000 right here.
What do you think?

01:18.496 --> 01:19.622
- Last call.
- We're out.

01:19.622 --> 01:20.831
Sold.
You got her.

01:20.831 --> 01:22.249
$130,000.
Thank you.

01:28.547 --> 01:31.550
♪ rock music ♪

01:31.550 --> 01:35.513
♪♪♪

01:35.513 --> 01:38.891
♪ Think of all
the luck you got ♪

01:38.891 --> 01:42.102
♪ Know that
it's not for naught ♪

01:42.102 --> 01:45.190
♪ You were beaming
once before ♪

01:45.190 --> 01:49.610
♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪

01:49.610 --> 01:52.905
♪ What is this downside ♪

01:52.905 --> 01:56.116
♪ That you speak of? ♪

01:56.116 --> 01:58.494
♪ What is this feeling ♪

01:58.494 --> 02:03.040
♪ You're so sure of? ♪

02:03.040 --> 02:08.045
♪♪♪

02:09.964 --> 02:13.176
♪ Round up
the friends you got ♪

02:13.176 --> 02:16.178
♪ Know that
they're not for naught ♪

02:16.178 --> 02:19.682
♪ You were willing
once before ♪

02:19.682 --> 02:24.019
♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪

02:24.019 --> 02:27.357
♪ What is this downside ♪

02:27.357 --> 02:30.985
♪ That you speak of? ♪

02:30.985 --> 02:32.903
♪ What is this feeling ♪

02:32.903 --> 02:37.616
♪ You're so sure of? ♪

02:37.616 --> 02:39.327
It's our crib.

02:39.327 --> 02:40.578
- Not anymore.
- [Carl] Who says?

02:40.578 --> 02:42.037
State of Illinois.

02:42.037 --> 02:43.539
They can't just
take it from us.

02:43.539 --> 02:45.958
I don't have time to explain
foreclosure law to you.

02:45.958 --> 02:48.419
Those are the stairs where I
broke my arm for the first time.

02:48.419 --> 02:50.380
Yeah, and the second.

02:50.380 --> 02:51.422
Oh, and the fifth.

02:51.422 --> 02:54.217
That table is where Liam
was born.

02:54.217 --> 02:55.217
[Fiona] There's nothing
we can do.

02:55.217 --> 02:56.260
[crashing]

02:56.260 --> 02:58.053
Can you keep it down in there?

02:58.053 --> 03:01.473
Copper pipes aren't gonna
take out themselves.

03:01.473 --> 03:03.183
While Rome burns,
you eat waffles.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.352
You gonna tear apart
the place piece by piece?

03:05.352 --> 03:07.230
Scorched earth.

03:07.230 --> 03:10.149
The preferred method of defeated
generals who refused to allow

03:10.149 --> 03:12.192
their conquerors
the satisfaction.

03:12.192 --> 03:13.360
Of taking a dump?

03:13.360 --> 03:15.321
Copper's two bucks a pound.

03:15.321 --> 03:17.489
Look, we don't have the luxury
to sit around and get weepy.

03:17.489 --> 03:18.949
We need a place to live.

03:18.949 --> 03:21.327
Let's see them try to
get Nick and I out.

03:21.327 --> 03:23.246
We'll take positions up at
the upstairs windows with M16s.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.080
Carl.

03:25.080 --> 03:27.207
Throw Liam at the bottom of
the stairs with some grenades.

03:27.207 --> 03:29.377
Think you can pull a pin
and throw it?

03:29.377 --> 03:30.336
Strap Chuckie up
with some explosives

03:30.336 --> 03:32.087
and throw him
off the roof.

03:32.087 --> 03:34.214
Do any of that and they'll
try you as an adult.

03:34.214 --> 03:35.591
That's big boy prison.

03:35.591 --> 03:37.468
Look, the house is gone.

03:37.468 --> 03:38.802
It's over.

03:38.802 --> 03:40.220
We need to move on.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.847
This is all cause of
the mud people.

03:41.847 --> 03:43.433
What the fuck?

03:43.433 --> 03:44.975
That's what my friends
in juvie said.

03:44.975 --> 03:47.227
[laughs]

03:47.227 --> 03:49.229
What?
What did I say?

03:49.229 --> 03:51.065
Chuckie, if you want
to stay alive,

03:51.065 --> 03:52.274
shut up and go to school.

03:54.319 --> 03:55.527
[groans]

03:57.821 --> 03:58.822
Where's Lip at?

03:58.822 --> 04:00.532
He'd back me up on this.

04:00.532 --> 04:01.825
I told him we didn't need him.

04:01.825 --> 04:03.452
He needs to focus on school.

04:03.452 --> 04:06.246
♪ upbeat rock music ♪

04:06.246 --> 04:08.415
[both groaning
and moaning]

04:08.415 --> 04:09.958
That's too much?

04:09.958 --> 04:11.627
No. Don't you dare stop.

04:11.627 --> 04:12.836
♪♪♪

04:12.836 --> 04:14.797
[books clattering]

04:14.797 --> 04:18.342
- [laughs]
- [laughing] Oh, my God.

04:18.342 --> 04:21.345
[both laughing]

04:21.345 --> 04:25.641
♪♪♪

04:25.641 --> 04:27.310
George, Betsy, let's go!

04:27.310 --> 04:30.438
I got 600 bags of fiberglass
coming today.

04:30.438 --> 04:32.147
Hold on, I got another call.

04:32.147 --> 04:34.400
Hey, Mark, I'll be on site
as soon as I can.

04:34.400 --> 04:35.484
Are you fricking kidding me?

04:35.484 --> 04:36.527
[toaster dings]

04:36.527 --> 04:38.153
Oh, no, no, no.
I got it.

04:38.153 --> 04:39.446
Jam or honey?

04:39.446 --> 04:41.657
- Jam, thank you.
- [Debbie] Of course.

04:41.657 --> 04:43.033
You got to eat before
you go to the hospital.

04:43.033 --> 04:44.493
Uh, sandwiches, chips,
and carrots,

04:44.493 --> 04:46.412
and Betsy, I put your cleats
in your backpack for soccer.

04:46.412 --> 04:47.663
[Tyler] Hold on, let me check
the budget.

04:47.663 --> 04:49.248
Okay.
[groans]

04:49.248 --> 04:51.041
There's too many people
in this house.

04:51.041 --> 04:53.127
No, we can't afford
two more laborers.

04:53.127 --> 04:54.379
Come on.
Bus isn't gonna wait.

04:54.379 --> 04:56.255
- All right, bye.
- Kisses.

04:56.255 --> 04:58.882
Hey, no fights today, Georgie.

04:58.882 --> 05:00.634
Hey, come here,
little one.

05:00.634 --> 05:01.593
Bye, babies.

05:01.593 --> 05:03.721
Hey, I'm serious, buddy.

05:03.721 --> 05:06.140
[car horn honks]

05:06.140 --> 05:07.850
Isn't Debbie great
with the kids?

05:07.850 --> 05:09.685
We don't need the teen mom
every morning.

05:09.685 --> 05:10.686
She's 18.

05:10.686 --> 05:12.104
[door closes]

05:12.104 --> 05:13.605
And it's only
a couple hours.

05:13.605 --> 05:15.149
Um, I'll start cleaning
up the dishes,

05:15.149 --> 05:16.817
and Betsy's sheets need washing.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.110
She wet the bed again?

05:18.110 --> 05:19.945
I'll start the laundry.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.739
Don't you have school
or something?

05:21.739 --> 05:23.532
Uh, not for a while,
so if you need any help,

05:23.532 --> 05:25.451
I'm available, Mr. Wexler.

05:25.451 --> 05:28.454
You're a nice girl, but keep
your resume handy.

05:28.454 --> 05:30.247
This isn't gonna be
a long-term gig.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.249
Of course.

05:32.249 --> 05:33.333
Oh, no!

05:33.333 --> 05:36.378
♪ rock music ♪

05:36.378 --> 05:38.088
♪♪♪

05:38.088 --> 05:39.548
[sighs] I got to go.

05:39.548 --> 05:44.553
♪♪♪

05:45.929 --> 05:47.723
Well, looks like
an earthquake hit.

05:47.723 --> 05:48.891
Hope we didn't tip off
the neighbors.

05:48.891 --> 05:50.684
Don't be late for class.

05:50.684 --> 05:52.352
You know, I'm not sure
I'm gonna be able to remember

05:52.352 --> 05:55.355
where the room is after
so many blows to my skull.

05:55.355 --> 05:57.566
You put "Atlas Shrugged"
on the top shelf?

05:57.566 --> 05:59.026
Hardcover?

05:59.026 --> 06:01.612
Aww, did Ayn Rand hurt
your poor little skull?

06:01.612 --> 06:03.489
You know, I'm pretty sure
she gave me a contusion.

06:03.489 --> 06:04.865
You should read it.

06:04.865 --> 06:06.033
She's got some interesting
things to say.

06:06.033 --> 06:07.535
Ah, no thanks.

06:07.535 --> 06:09.161
Every Libertarian was born
on third base

06:09.161 --> 06:11.955
and thinks he hit a triple.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.416
All right.

06:13.416 --> 06:15.876
What about Klimt then?

06:15.876 --> 06:17.503
I got it for you.

06:17.503 --> 06:18.587
Those paintings I mentioned.

06:18.587 --> 06:20.881
Prepare to have
your mind blown.

06:20.881 --> 06:23.592
I'll, uh, I'll check it out.

06:25.344 --> 06:27.095
What?

06:27.095 --> 06:29.515
No...nothing.

06:29.515 --> 06:32.309
[chuckles]

06:32.309 --> 06:35.312
♪ rock music ♪

06:35.312 --> 06:40.317
♪♪♪

06:44.238 --> 06:46.532
Theo's going out of town
for work.

06:46.532 --> 06:47.825
♪♪♪

06:47.825 --> 06:49.619
Keep me company tonight?

06:49.619 --> 06:54.624
♪♪♪

06:57.209 --> 07:00.295
Lord Jesus, thank you for
bringing us together

07:00.295 --> 07:03.549
to study your word
and bask in your glory.

07:03.549 --> 07:05.551
- Amen.
- [all] Amen.

07:05.551 --> 07:08.595
Who else would like to show
the Lord his gratitude?

07:08.595 --> 07:09.596
Right here, Carol.

07:09.596 --> 07:11.223
[child exclaims]

07:11.223 --> 07:13.016
Lord, please let
my baby girls grow up

07:13.016 --> 07:16.562
to have wicked backhands
and 120 mile-per-hour serves.

07:16.562 --> 07:18.230
This is Bible study, Kevin.

07:18.230 --> 07:21.441
We're here to praise Jesus,
not ask him for favors.

07:22.652 --> 07:23.986
Right.
Right, I'm sorry.

07:23.986 --> 07:26.154
Can I just do
one more real quick?

07:26.154 --> 07:30.450
Jesus, please help Yanis rest
in peace so I can get some rest

07:30.450 --> 07:33.663
and not have panic attacks,

07:33.663 --> 07:35.539
and not soil my pants.

07:35.539 --> 07:37.500
- Is that everybody?
- [all] Yes.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.459
Well, I'll see you next week.

07:39.459 --> 07:41.587
There's coffee and muffins
in the kitchen.

07:41.587 --> 07:42.838
They're a day old,
but no mold.

07:42.838 --> 07:44.590
I checked.
Praise Jesus.

07:44.590 --> 07:47.301
Oh, and don't forget, we still
need a volunteer to host

07:47.301 --> 07:49.511
the foster child we're
receiving this morning.

07:49.511 --> 07:51.305
Thank you for coming.

07:51.305 --> 07:52.640
- We'll take him.
- What?

07:52.640 --> 07:54.559
Bless you, Kevin.

07:54.559 --> 07:56.476
He's on his way from Myanmar
to a dairy farm in Wisconsin.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.563
Oh, it--it--it's only for
a couple of days.

07:58.563 --> 08:00.439
Oh, this is--praise Jesus.

08:00.439 --> 08:03.066
Thank you.
Oh.

08:03.066 --> 08:04.401
The hell you doing?

08:04.401 --> 08:05.777
It's a kid in need.

08:05.777 --> 08:07.572
If I do God a solid,
he'll do me one.

08:07.572 --> 08:08.822
Eye for an eye.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.657
That is not what
"eye for an eye" means.

08:10.657 --> 08:12.868
Oh, how do you know what
the good book means?

08:12.868 --> 08:14.286
You were doing your nails
the whole time.

08:14.286 --> 08:15.495
Forget that barbecued Greek.

08:15.495 --> 08:17.039
It wasn't your fault.

08:17.039 --> 08:18.874
Of course it was.
What are you talking about, V?

08:18.874 --> 08:22.712
If it wasn't for me,
Yanis would still be alive.

08:22.712 --> 08:24.796
Please, baby.

08:27.049 --> 08:30.052
[electricity crackling]

08:31.053 --> 08:32.846
Whoo.

08:32.846 --> 08:34.932
If I go along with getting
a new crib, it better be sick.

08:34.932 --> 08:36.600
We can't pay any more
than we already were.

08:36.600 --> 08:38.810
We were barely making ends
meet as it was.

08:38.810 --> 08:40.688
Why you acting like
we ain't got no lettuce?

08:40.688 --> 08:42.064
Lettuce?

08:42.064 --> 08:43.273
The Benjamins.

08:43.273 --> 08:45.067
Cash.
Money.

08:45.067 --> 08:46.902
Say the word, and I'll make it
rain up in here.

08:46.902 --> 08:49.237
I told you, I'm not taking
your dirty money.

08:49.237 --> 08:52.366
It must be wonderful living
in your little fantasy world

08:52.366 --> 08:56.119
where unicorns slide down
magical rainbows and everybody

08:56.119 --> 08:58.581
on the South Side gets by
on the up and up.

08:58.581 --> 09:00.791
What do you think this
neighborhood runs on?

09:00.791 --> 09:02.710
It ain't donuts.

09:02.710 --> 09:05.545
Without heroes like Carl here
driving our shadow economy,

09:05.545 --> 09:08.548
we would've gone the way
of the dodo years ago.

09:08.548 --> 09:11.677
Hey, can I, um, can I get
a relocation advance?

09:11.677 --> 09:12.803
Thank you.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.766
Yo!
What the hell?

09:16.766 --> 09:20.352
I didn't realize the house
was still occupied.

09:20.352 --> 09:21.895
Oh, shit.

09:21.895 --> 09:23.355
You're the new owners.

09:23.355 --> 09:24.856
We're just here to take
a few measurements

09:24.856 --> 09:26.858
for the kids' beds,
tile for the bathroom.

09:26.858 --> 09:28.944
We're in the process
of moving out,

09:28.944 --> 09:31.739
but been here since
before I was born.

09:31.739 --> 09:33.115
It's a lot of stuff
to get together.

09:33.115 --> 09:34.700
Contractors aren't coming
till next week

09:34.700 --> 09:36.410
if you want to take your time.

09:36.410 --> 09:38.495
Thanks.
That's really nice of you.

09:38.495 --> 09:40.122
Hey.

09:40.122 --> 09:44.627
You ever seen what a machete
can do to the human body?

09:44.627 --> 09:46.003
He's kidding.

09:46.003 --> 09:47.630
Let's get to school, huh?

09:47.630 --> 09:49.715
Come on.
I'll drop off Liam.

09:53.761 --> 09:55.595
We'll just go up and look
at the bedrooms.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.597
[Ruby squeals]
I get the biggest one.

09:57.597 --> 09:59.433
[Matilda] No way, I do!

10:02.436 --> 10:05.022
[door slams shut]

10:05.022 --> 10:06.481
You all right?

10:06.481 --> 10:08.483
It's the hormones.

10:08.483 --> 10:10.610
I'm trying not to think
about it.

10:10.610 --> 10:13.155
It's hard losing the house
you've lived in your whole life.

10:13.155 --> 10:17.409
It's just a pile of wood
and plaster.

10:17.409 --> 10:19.411
I called you.
We had a family meeting.

10:19.411 --> 10:20.746
I had work.

10:20.746 --> 10:21.872
You got a job?

10:21.872 --> 10:23.957
Yeah, I have to support
my family.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.375
And to answer
your next question,

10:25.375 --> 10:26.669
yes, I'm still going to school.

10:26.669 --> 10:27.836
I'm responsible like that.

10:27.836 --> 10:30.005
- I'm gonna find us a new place.
- So?

10:30.005 --> 10:32.841
It's not like me and my baby
will be welcome there.

10:32.841 --> 10:34.217
It's not out of your womb yet.

10:34.217 --> 10:35.677
You can still stay
under my roof.

10:35.677 --> 10:37.679
[scoffs]
Splitting hairs, aren't you?

10:37.679 --> 10:40.515
It's my job to tell you when
you're making a huge mistake.

10:40.515 --> 10:41.851
[Frank] Don't listen
to that baby killer.

10:41.851 --> 10:43.560
Shut up, Frank!

10:43.560 --> 10:45.645
I am way past when any doctor
would do an abortion anyway,

10:45.645 --> 10:47.105
so just save it, Fiona.

10:47.105 --> 10:49.316
There are other options.
Adoption.

10:49.316 --> 10:51.735
You'd give away a Gallagher?

10:51.735 --> 10:54.571
For free?
Shame on you.

10:54.571 --> 10:57.240
Just answer your phone
when I call, will you?

10:59.785 --> 11:03.663
Pay no attention
to your homicidal sister.

11:03.663 --> 11:04.664
Coffee?

11:04.664 --> 11:06.666
Can't, it's bad for the baby.

11:06.666 --> 11:09.712
No, for me.

11:09.712 --> 11:11.463
We have to speed things up.

11:11.463 --> 11:13.548
You've got to convince
the dying mom

11:13.548 --> 11:15.342
that they need you
full-time.

11:15.342 --> 11:17.469
Well, Mrs. Wexler
already loves me.

11:17.469 --> 11:19.221
So convince the husband.

11:19.221 --> 11:21.348
I've been busting my ass trying
to prove to Mr. Wexler

11:21.348 --> 11:22.850
that I'd be a great wife,

11:22.850 --> 11:24.267
and he just doesn't
want me there.

11:24.267 --> 11:26.686
That's because you're not
being a great wife,

11:26.686 --> 11:28.480
you're being a great nanny.

11:28.480 --> 11:30.732
Nobody wants
to fuck Mary Poppins.

11:30.732 --> 11:31.900
[sighs]

11:31.900 --> 11:33.903
What am I supposed to do?

11:33.903 --> 11:37.782
See to his needs.
All his needs.

11:37.782 --> 11:39.742
But I've tried sexy before.

11:39.742 --> 11:40.867
It's never worked,

11:40.867 --> 11:42.786
and that was before
I had cankles.

11:42.786 --> 11:44.913
Nonsense.
You're glowing.

11:44.913 --> 11:47.499
And remember what my mother
said: "A hole's a hole."

11:47.499 --> 11:49.919
A guy doesn't really care
who's attached to it.

11:49.919 --> 11:51.336
[chuckles]
Sounds like Grammy.

11:51.336 --> 11:53.839
Besides, you think after
a day of radiation,

11:53.839 --> 11:55.507
cancer girl's getting
on her knees?

11:55.507 --> 11:57.759
She hasn't given it up
for months.

11:57.759 --> 12:00.595
The husband would probably blow
his wad if you shake his hand.

12:03.473 --> 12:04.641
What happened to the wall?

12:04.641 --> 12:05.851
Mind your own business.

12:05.851 --> 12:06.893
You smell like a toilet.

12:06.893 --> 12:08.771
Beat it, brat!

12:08.771 --> 12:10.272
Mom!

12:10.272 --> 12:12.023
What time's the soon-to-be
widower get home?

12:12.023 --> 12:14.025
Late afternoon.

12:14.025 --> 12:16.778
Okay, when the family's away,
you take care of your man.

12:16.778 --> 12:20.490
I guarantee you, he'll move you
into the guest room in no time.

